title: For Sale:  PVS7C
postcontent:
The PVS-7 is the tried and true US Military Night Vision goggle system that is still relied upon by US Military and Law Enforcement forces. 

Night Vision Goggles, AN/PVS-7C, is a self-contained night vision system worn on the head or hand-held, providing  improved night vision capabilities using available light from the night sky (starlight, moonlight). They may be used with or without the standard battle helmet and chemical-biological mask, and provide capabilities for reading, forming manual tasks, patrolling, walking and surveillance. The AN/PVS-7C is submersible. 

The goggles can be used in cloudy starlight to bright moonlight. They can be removed quiclky from the facemask with automatic shut-off. They can be detached from the facemask and used as a hand-held viewer. The goggles are held in their normal lowered position by a spring-loaded detent. In extreme darkness, the goggles have an infared feature that allows viewing at close range. 

Night Vision Goggles, AN/PVS-7C, have an eye span adjustment that permits the eyepiece lenses to be moved in line with an operator's eyes. The adjustment is made by moving the eyepiece lenses apart or closer together until a single, clear, circular field of view is obtained. The eye relief adjustment permits the goggles to be moved in or out on the facemask carriage to a position approximately 2.5 cm (one inch) from the operator's eyes without losing a field of view. Thei permits the operator to wear a protective mask or most eyeglasses while wearing the goggles. 

They have a quick release feature and automatic shut-off. the goggles may be used on or off the facemask. To use the goggles on the facemask, mount the goggles on the carriage, insert the slide into the carriage and press firmly until a click is heard. To release the goggles from the carriage, press the button on the top front of the carriage and pull the goggles away from the face. If the goggles are removed from the facemask while turned on, the automatic shut-off feature will turn off the goggles. The goggles will operate if the rotary switch was not turned on to another position while they were on the facemask. 

Operates on 2 “AA” or 1 ea. BA5557/U Battery (Up to 40 hours continuous run time on 2 AA batteries) 
Automatic Brightness Control (ABC) 
Built-In IR Illuminator (acts as a flashlight that can only be seen through the NVGs) 
High Light Cutoff Tube Protection 
Waterproof (down to 20 meters)

postcontent: This is a extremely nice collectors piece. The is an Volunteer Open Bolt 45acp in all its glory, all original, open bolt. Shit on those 1500.00 Mac 10's, 9's bullet hose pistols. This is serial numbered 0392. This makes it the right near the starting gate of the round open bolt Volunteer series. Through some studies of serial #'s I figure only a few thousand were made. Too, there were a lot of these guns that over the years have been lost,destroyed,broken, etc. After all, back in the 60's you could have one for less than 200.00 JUDGE FOR YOURSELF, AN EXTREMELY PRETTY GUN. ALSO LIKE THE EAGLE MK I&2, THESE CAN TAKE A FULL AUTO GREASE GUN BOLT WHERE YOU DON'T HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT EXTRACTORS BREAKING Thank god the government never went after the above mentioned class's of guns. They did grab the Spitfire which was also produced as a semi open bolt gun and reclassified it as a SMG. This was due to the ease of conversion for one. This gun and the Spitfire SMG are identical guns both inside and out. Anyway getting back to the gun, it has been shot but by its looks is in remarkable shape. Few handling scratches here and there but a well built shooter for the rest of it's life. Takes .45 M3A1 grease gun mags which are everywhere. Besides the M-16, the Grease gun mag was probably one of the most manufactured US military mags. Is this the gun for You? No? Well take the stock off and shoot it. YES!! YOU CAN LEGALLY TAKE THE STOCK OFF AND STILL HAVE A RIFLE WITH AN OAL OF 27 1/4" THIS GUN IS HISTORIC NOW AND WILL ONLY GAIN IN VALUE, SHOT OR NOT. Has not been made since the 60's which puts it at 50 years old or so. AND remember, Open Bolt Guns can no longer be produced and have not been for decades Thanks for looking. NOTE there is no trade.

title: For Sale:  Hornady Action Pistol (HAP) Bullets 45 Caliber (451 Diameter) 230 Grain
postcontent:
100 for $25

The bullet engineered with the competitive shooter in mind. Hornady began with a bullet legendary in its accuracy - the Hornady XTP - and redesigned it as the perfect competition projectile. While the XTP uses folds and a cannelure to aid in expansion and increase terminal performance, expansion is meaningless in competition. So, the folds and cannelure are gone from the HAP (Hornady Action Pistol) bullet. 

Because jamming can cost a competitive shooter the match, Hornady placed the HAP's pure lead core inside a copper jacket that protects the nose, ensuring smooth feeding. And like the XTP, the core of the HAP bullet is cold swaged from pure lead to give it amazing consistence, balance and stability in flight. This is not loaded ammunition.
